President Trump held a press conference in the Rose Garden to discuss the ongoing government shutdown and border security. He highlighted the recent job growth numbers, wage growth, and the success of trade negotiations with China, Canada, Mexico, and South Korea. He reiterated his commitment to border security and building a wall or steel barrier along the southern border. He mentioned the need for stronger ports of entry and described the dangers of illegal immigration, including drug trafficking and human trafficking. He also discussed the possibility of using emergency powers to fund the wall and expressed confidence in reaching a deal with Democrats.